## 12) LUNCH-SYSTEM-SPECIFIC HIERARCHY

For combo cards, formula pages, and ingredient systems, preserve this scan order:

1. lunch track
2. total protein
3. what the lunch is
4. ingredient amounts / component structure
5. prep time / cost band
6. use case
7. friction notes: smell, mess, utensils, carry
8. sauce or flavor support last

### 12.1 Combo-card rules
- use an identical shell across all cards
- total protein must appear in the same place every time
- track tag must be instantly visible
- ingredient lines must be compact and aligned
- format labels may be more visible on minimal-cooler pages
- decoration must not consume text space

### 12.2 Practical-friction signals
Use when relevant:
- Low Mess / Higher Mess
- Low Smell / Noticeable Smell
- No Fork / Fork Needed
- Fast Pack
- Better Packed Cold
- Long Day
- Short Break
- Packet / Shelf-Stable
- Optional / Pack Cold

### 12.3 Sauce rule
If sauce appears:
- keep it low in the hierarchy
- show one practical pairing only
- prefer packet logic
- never make sauce the hero

